{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_5","type":"command_execution","command":"\"C:\\\\Program Files\\\\PowerShell\\\\7\\\\pwsh.exe\" -Command \"Get-Content -Raw 'C:\\\\Users\\\\jairo\\\\.codex\\\\plugins\\\\cache\\\\openai-curated-remote\\\\superpowers\\\\6.1.1\\\\skills\\\\using-superpowers\\\\references\\\\codex-tools.md'; git status --short; git log -5 --oneline; rg --files frontend docs | Sort-Object; Get-Content -Raw 'docs\\\\frontend-specification-v2.md'; Get-Content -Raw 'docs\\\\frontend-implementation-plan-v2.md'; Get-Content -Raw 'docs\\\\frontend-tasks-v2.md'\"","aggregated_output":"## Subagent dispatch requires multi-agent support\n\nAdd to your Codex config (`~/.codex/config.toml`):\n\n```toml\n[features]\nmulti_agent = true\n```\n\nThis enables `spawn_agent`, `wait_agent`, and `close_agent` for skills like `dispatching-parallel-agents` and `subagent-driven-development`. When using subagent-driven-development, you should always close implementer and reviewer subagents when they have finished all their work.\n\n## Environment Detection\n\nSkills that create worktrees or finish branches should detect their\nenvironment with read-only git commands before proceeding:\n\n```bash\nGIT_DIR=$(cd \"$(git rev-parse --git-dir)\" 2>/dev/null && pwd -P)\nGIT_COMMON=$(cd \"$(git rev-parse --git-common-dir)\" 2>/dev/null && pwd -P)\nBRANCH=$(git branch --show-current)\n```\n\n- `GIT_DIR != GIT_COMMON` → already in a linked worktree (skip creation)\n- `BRANCH` empty → detached HEAD (cannot branch/push/PR from sandbox)\n\nSee `using-git-worktrees` Step 0 and `finishing-a-development-branch`\nStep 1 for how each skill uses these signals.\n\n## Codex App Finishing\n\nWhen the sandbox blocks branch/push operations (detached HEAD in an\nexternally managed worktree), the agent commits all work and informs\nthe user to use the App's native controls:\n\n- **\"Create branch\"** — names the branch, then commit/push/PR via App UI\n- **\"Hand off to local\"** — transfers work to the user's local checkout\n\nThe agent can still run tests, stage files, and output suggested branch\nnames, commit messages, and PR descriptions for the user to copy.\n\r\n?? .codex-runs/TASK-052.codex.log\n?? .codex-runs/TASK-052.prompt.md\nb3f33bc feat(TASK-051): Implementar ProductCard apenas com dados suportados pelo OpenAPI.\n4b14493 feat(TASK-050): Implementar parser e serializer da URL para busca, categoria e página.\n52dfb01 feat(TASK-049): Implementar query de produtos por `categoriaId`.\n67f7c9a feat(TASK-048): Implementar query paginada de catálogo com `page`, `size` e `searchword`.\n55d0496 feat(TASK-047): Implementar query de categorias com cache apropriado.\ndocs\\api-implementation-plan.md\r\ndocs\\api-reference.md\r\ndocs\\architecture.md\r\ndocs\\decisions\\2026-07-08-enderecos-v1.md\r\ndocs\\decisions\\2026-07-10-task-030-auth-session-storage-abstraction.md\r\ndocs\\domain-modeling.md\r\ndocs\\frontend-backlog.md\r\ndocs\\frontend-implementation-plan-v2.md\r\ndocs\\frontend-implementation-plan.md\r\ndocs\\frontend-specification-v2.md\r\ndocs\\frontend-specs.md\r\ndocs\\frontend-tasks-v2.md\r\ndocs\\frontend-test-fix-report-2026-07-13.md\r\ndocs\\ideacao\\carrinho.html\r\ndocs\\ideacao\\dados.html\r\ndocs\\ideacao\\guia.html\r\ndocs\\ideacao\\index.html\r\ndocs\\ideacao\\js\\app.js\r\ndocs\\ideacao\\js\\layout.js\r\ndocs\\ideacao\\js\\theme.js\r\ndocs\\ideacao\\login.html\r\ndocs\\ideacao\\pedidos.html\r\ndocs\\ideacao\\produto.html\r\ndocs\\ideacao\\senha.html\r\nfrontend\\e2e\\smoke.spec.ts\r\nfrontend\\eslint.config.js\r\nfrontend\\index.html\r\nfrontend\\package-lock.json\r\nfrontend\\package.json\r\nfrontend\\playwright-report\\index.html\r\nfrontend\\playwright.config.ts\r\nfrontend\\public\\mockServiceWorker.js\r\nfrontend\\src\\App.test.tsx\r\nfrontend\\src\\App.tsx\r\nfrontend\\src\\app\\layouts\\AccountLayout.tsx\r\nfrontend\\src\\app\\layouts\\Footer.test.tsx\r\nfrontend\\src\\app\\layouts\\Footer.tsx\r\nfrontend\\src\\app\\layouts